ess to their metadata and that top-level test classes are public. If I modify the test file to add necessary methods, it should avoid the need to re-test everything. I’m also considering how to correctly reference nested module names dynamically. This should clarify things!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying nested object naming**\\n\\nI’m considering that the enclosing object class name might be `Container$` and the nested object could be `Container$NestedModule$`. I need to verify this in Scala’s structure, where objects like `Outer` contain `Inner`. It seems I should expect class names like `Outer$.class` and `Outer$Inner$.class`, possibly even `Outer$Inner.class`. I also need to use specific naming conventions for dynamic access, like including a dollar sign between package names for accurate reference. This should keep things clear!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2fROIh36DtQBApyFT7B14kMp|fc_0041883fae2ba52d0169fb459c316881948e094eddda1e6394", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.portable-scala/portable-scala-reflect_2.13/1.1.1/src/test/scala/org_portable_scala/portable_scala_reflect_2_13/Portable_scala_reflect_2_13Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "  @Test\n  def unwrapsExceptionsThrownWhileLoadingModules(): Unit = {\n    val reflected = requireFound(\n      Reflect.lookupLoadableModuleClass(topLevelModuleName(\"ThrowingModule\"), loader),\n      \"throwing module should be discoverable before it is loaded\")\n\n    assertThatThrownBy(throwing {\n      reflected.loadModule()\n    }).isInstanceOf(classOf[IllegalStateException])\n      .hasMessage(\"module failed\")\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def currentClassLoaderMacroOverloadsDelegateToExplicitLookup(): Unit = {", "newText": "  @Test\n  def unwrapsExceptionsThrownWhileLoadingModules(): Unit = {\n    val reflected = requireFound(\n      Reflect.lookupLoadableModuleClass(topLevelModuleName(\"ThrowingModule\"), loader),\n      \"throwing module should be discoverable before it is loaded\")\n\n    assertThatThrownBy(throwing {\n      reflected.loadModule()\n    }).isInstanceOf(classOf[IllegalStateException])\n      .hasMessage(\"module failed\")\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def loadsAnnotatedModulesNestedInsideStaticObjects(): Unit = {\n    val moduleName = s\"$testPackageName.StaticModuleContainer$$NestedEnabledModule$$\"\n    val reflected = requireFound(\n      Reflect.lookupLoadableModuleClass(moduleName, loader),\n      \"annotated module nested inside a static object should be discoverable\")\n\n    assertThat(reflected.runtimeClass.getName).isEqualTo(moduleName)\n    val module = reflected.loadModule().asInstanceOf[ModuleApi]\n    assertThat(module.describe(\"portable\")).isEqualTo(\"nested:portable\")\n    assertThat(module).isSameAs(StaticModuleContainer.NestedEnabledModule)\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def currentClassLoaderMacroOverloadsDelegateToExplicitLookup(): Unit = {"}, {"oldText": "object UnannotatedModule extends ModuleApi {\n  override def describe(value: String): String = s\"unannotated:$value\"\n}\n\n@EnableReflectiveInstantiation\nobject ThrowingModule {", "newText": "object UnannotatedModule extends ModuleApi {\n  override def describe(value: String): String = s\"unannotated:$value\"\n}\n\nobject StaticModuleContainer {\n  @EnableReflectiveInstantiation\n  object NestedEnabledModule extends ModuleApi {\n    override def describe(value: String): String = s\"nested:$value\"\n  }\n}\n\n@EnableReflectiveInstantiation\nobject ThrowingModule {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1003, "output": 1475, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27566, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778075019924, "responseId": "resp_0041883fae2ba52d0169fb458cd47881948002a152d61eddc5"}}
